Interface InstructionInstance

All Superinterfaces:
Comparable<InstructionInstance>
All Known Implementing Classes:
AbstractInstructionInstance
public interface InstructionInstance
extends Comparable<InstructionInstance>
Represents a (dynamic) instance of an Instruction.
Author:
Clemens Hammacher

  • Method Details

    • getInstruction

      Instruction getInstruction()
      Returns the Instruction that this InstructionInstance is an instance of.
      Returns:
      the Instruction of this instance

    • getInstanceNr

      long getInstanceNr()
      Returns the number of this instance. In backward traversal, it counts upwards from 0 on, in forward traversal reversed, so that the numbering is always consistent.
      Returns:
      the number of this instance

    • getOccurrenceNumber

      long getOccurrenceNumber()
      Returns the occurrence number of this instance. It always counts upwards from 0 on, so the numbering is in reverse order when traversing a trace backwards.
      Returns:
      the occurrence number of this instance

    • getStackDepth

      int getStackDepth()
      Returns the stack depth at which this instance occurred. The stack depth is always greater than zero.
      Returns:
      the stack depth at which this instance occurred

    • getAdditionalInfo

      InstructionInstanceInfo getAdditionalInfo()
      Returns additonal information which corresponds to this InstructionInstance. The kind of information depends of the type of the corresponding instruction (getInstruction().getType()):
      • for InstructionType.ARRAY, it's an ArrayInstruction.ArrayInstrInstanceInfo
      • for InstructionType.FIELD, it's an FieldInstruction.FieldInstrInstanceInfo
      • for InstructionType.NEWARRAY, it's an NewArrayInstruction.NewArrayInstrInstanceInfo
      • for InstructionType.MULTIANEWARRAY, it's an MultiANewArrayInstruction.MultiANewArrayInstrInstanceInfo
      • for InstructionType.TYPE, it's an TypeInstruction.TypeInstrInstanceInfo
      • for the rest, this method returns null
      Returns:
      additional information for this InstructionInstance
